Charmayne Maxwell, a member of the R&B group Brownstone in the 1990s, has died after a mysterious fall. 

Maxwell was attending a soccer game in Los Angeles when she fell. Her death has been described as an 'accident' by Danish media Her & Nu, which broke the news. 

The songstress was married to Danish music producer Carsten Soulshock and leaves behind a son named Nicolaj. 

